**1) React.memo** for components that render same output with same props:
```jsx
const MyComponent = React.memo(({ data }) => {
  return <div>{data}</div>;
});
```

**2) useCallback** for functions passed as props:
```jsx
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  doSomething(id);
}, [id]); // Only changes when id changes
```

**3) useMemo** for expensive calculations:
```jsx
const expensiveValue = useMemo(() => {
  return computeExpensiveValue(data);
}, [data]);
```

**4) State colocation**: Move state down to only components that need it
```jsx
// Bad: state in parent of many unrelated components
// Good: Lift state to nearest common ancestor or use context
```

**5) Key properly in lists** (stable, unique, not index unless static):
```jsx
{items.map(item => <Item key={item.id} item={item} />)}
```

**6) Avoid inline objects/functions in render**:
```jsx
// Bad (new object every render)
<Component style={{ margin: 10 }} />

// Good
const style = { margin: 10 };
<Component style={style} />
```

**7) Virtualize long lists** (react-window, react-virtualized):
```jsx
import { FixedSizeList } from 'react-window';
<FixedSizeList height={400} itemCount={10000} itemSize={35}>
  {Row}
</FixedSizeList>
```

**8) Split context** (multiple contexts for unrelated data):
```jsx
// Bad (everything in one context)
// Good: UserContext, ThemeContext, SettingsContext separate
```

